What I Do
Solo Piano & Keyboards
I perform solo piano with a strong jazz focus, while mixing in a variety of styles depending on the event and audience.
For clients who want a fuller sound, I can use keyboards to create the feel of a small group, incorporating bass, drums, and string textures. It's an especially good option when you'd like the sound and energy of a band while keeping costs down.
I'm also a strong sight-reader and have extensive experience performing for:
	•	Theatre productions
	•	Church services
	•	Wedding ceremonies
	•	Vocalists and instrumentalists requiring accompaniment
Duo & Trio Performances
Smaller groups are often a great balance of sound, flexibility, and budget.
Available configurations include:
	•	Piano and drums (listen here)
	•	Piano and bass
	•	Piano and vocalist
	•	Piano and horn players
I also perform regularly with jazz trios throughout Atlanta, including more than 30 years with the Atlanta Jazz Trio (listen here).
Larger Groups
For events that call for a bigger sound, I can provide several ensemble options:
Atlanta Jazz Quartet
	•	Available with our vocalist or saxophonist
	•	Ideal for receptions, corporate events, and private parties
The Atlanta Crawdaddies
	•	A New Orleans-inspired group featuring 1–4 horns
	•	Repertoire includes jazz, blues, R&B, classic rock, and some country
	•	Learn more here

On the Day of Your Event
I perform at many events every year, but on the day of your event, that's my focus.
I'm meticulous about preparation, so you can expect:
	•	Arrival and setup with plenty of time to spare
	•	Time built in for traffic, sound checks, and last-minute adjustments
	•	Backup keyboard, speaker, and cables on-site
	•	Backup copies of any special music you've requested
My goal is simple: provide great music and make sure everything runs smoothly.